700716f-b.text:
(1)
Cauldwell Avenue, east side, south from (No. 624) Westchester Avenue to E. 149th Street. View 1 shows the block extending only about three-quarters of the way to the E. 149th Street, at which point it begins to decline.

June 25, 1938.
P. L. Sperr.

(2)
Continuing southward toward E. 149th Street from the point where the street begins to decline in view 1.

June 25, 1938.
P. L. Sperr.

(3)
The same section of the block seen in view 2, as viewed in the opposite direction from E. 149th Street.

June 25, 1938.
P. L. Sperr.

(1)
Cauldwell Avenue, at the N.E. corner of Westchester Avenue,
showing Lebanon Hospital.
June 25, 1938.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
Viewing the hospital in the opposite direction; southward
toward Westchester Avenue.
June 25, 1938.
P. L. Sperr.
(3)

looking toward Westchester Avenue.
June 25, 1938.
